Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.16,0:00:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Cáo Cāo's large army experienced\Nmore than one month of tedious battles.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.83,0:00:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They eventually conquered\NShòuchūn and routed Yuán Shù.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.10,0:00:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,At this time, Zhāng Xiù and Liú Biǎo
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.60,0:00:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,took advantage of Cáo Cāo's absence\Nfrom Xǔdū to attack the Central Plains.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.91,0:00:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Cáo Cāo was forced to lead\Nhis army to defend Xǔdū.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.75,0:00:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,On the 3rd year of the Jiàn'ān era, three more\Ninvasions against Zhāng Xi commenced.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.75,0:00:55.00,Header,,0,0,0,,Note: 198-199 AD
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.75,0:00:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Cáo Cāo's army is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.10,0:01:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Run away! Run away!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.14,0:01:09.22,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(589,355)\fade(255,0,255,0,350,2700,3060)}Cáo Cāo\NStyled: Mèngdé
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.30,0:01:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Send someone, to inform\Nall the villagers, far or near,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.61,0:01:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that I was ordered by the Emperor\Nto send an army against a rebellion!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.31,0:01:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it coincides with the\Nharvest season, Lieutenant.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.47,0:01:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to go through the wheat,\Nbut whoever tramples them...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.74,0:01:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,must be beheaded.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.89,0:01:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.42,0:01:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,With strict orders, the people can safely\Nharvest wheat; no need to be anxious.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.20,0:01:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.24,0:01:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Halt!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.97,0:01:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,My orders are utmostly important,\Nso you ought to be careful and obey it as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.34,0:01:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.54,0:03:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is the Provost Marshal?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.90,0:03:03.66,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(596,332)}The\NProvost Marshal
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.84,0:03:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.08,0:03:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,My horse trampled the wheat;\Nhow shall I be punished?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.25,0:03:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Prime Minister, how can I punish you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.62,0:03:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If I knew the law and broke it, but was absolved,\Nhow could the masses trust us?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.10,0:03:21.58,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(600,375)\fade(255,0,255,0,350,1900,1900)}Guō Jiā\NStyled: Fèngxiào
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.20,0:03:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Prime Minister! Prime Minister!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.46,0:03:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.31,0:03:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not oppose my orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.85,0:03:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(355.429,436.857)}Sir, during the Autumn and Spring period, \Nthose laws were not applied to the venerated.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.35,0:04:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(355.429,436.857)}Sir, you lead a grand army.\NHow could you harm yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.51,0:04:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Prime Minister! Prime Minister!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.26,0:04:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(355.429,436.857)}Since the Spring and Autumn laws\Ndo not apply to those of esteem,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.48,0:04:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(355.429,436.857)}I will not execute myself for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.82,0:04:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Prime Minister!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.15,0:04:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(355.429,436.857)}However, military orders are like mountains,\Nso although I shall be spared,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.15,0:04:55.78,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,This idiom means that military orders cannot be violated, just like how mountains cannot be moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.20,0:04:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(355.429,436.857)}I shall substitute my head with my hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.66,0:05:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Prime Minister.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.12,0:05:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.06,0:05:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,20 lǐ ahead is Wǎnchéng.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.60,0:05:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is Yùshuǐ-river?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.00,0:05:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We are on the right side of a grand mound.\NYùshuǐ River is below it.
Comment: 0,0:05:36.00,0:05:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Please review this: 等上右方高岗 育水便在脚下
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.82,0:06:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(355.429,436.857)\i1}Like a solitary leaf in the wind, I wither.
